div.entryFree: a - cf. etiam an -, on -, ond-, un-.
a: a fordh (E, a forthe A minus recte) in dies crudesceret. Cf. gisettan s. v. gisettae.
aad rogus. Cf. beel vel aad.
acuaerna vel sciron disperdulus. Cf. aqueorna.
adexa et adexe (illud L habet V, 418, 66, non adexe) lacerta.
aduinendanan, afulodan, asuundnan tabida et putrefacta. Cf. afulat ond asuunden.
aec þan (E, aec don A) quin etiam.
aectath (E, aechtath A) perpendit s. v. perpendo.
aeggimang (E, -mong A) ogastrum (vocem celticam agnoscit Schlutter).
aehrian (E, aegrihan A, i. e. aehnan vel aegnan) quisquiliae.
aelifnae alumnis E post V, 343, 3 (deest in Thes. s. v. alumnus, ad alumen alii referunt obloquende Schluttero in Anglia N. F. XIV, 297).
aemil curculio; gurgulio s. v. curculio.
aend suilcae (E, end suilce A) atque.
aengiþinga (E, -dinga A) quoque (A, quoquo E) modo.
aenid (E, aenit A) aneta s. v. anas 1.
aeohed eviscerata s. v. evisceratus (athed Gl. Corp. Chr.)
aesc (E, aastc A) fraxinus, aesc (E, esc A) praxinus s. v. fraxinus, aesc cerciclus s. v. cercurus.
aesctbrotae (E, -drotae A) ferola s. v. ferula.
aetrinan v. tha uuannan aetrinan s. v. uuannā.
aetsa (= adesa) dolatorium, etsa (et aecsa) ascia.
aferidae v. an uueg aferidae s. v. an.
afulat ond asuunden (A, aduinendanan, afulodan, asuundnan E) tabida et putrefacta.
afyred olbenda (C, afyrid obbenda A) dromidus.
agnaettae (E, agnetae A) usurpavit s. v. usurpo.
agnidinne (A, -dine C) de triturigine (Oros. VII, 25, 10 detrita rubigine con­fert Schlutter. v. p. 437).
algiuueorc (E, algiuerc A) ignarium s. v. igniarius.
ambaer (E, ombar A) urna, ainbaer (E, enƀ A) situla, ambras cados s. v. cadus.
ambect (E, ambaet A) rationator (rationato codd., unde alii rationatio), ambechtae collatio.
an - cf. etiam a -, and-, on -, ond-, un-.
an: an landae (A, on laste Gl. Corp. Chr. m. 1) e vestigio, an uueg aferidae (E, anuoega ueridae A) avehit s. v. aveho, an ba halbae (E, on ba halbe A) altrinsecus.
anhriosith (E, onhrisit A minus recte) ingruerit s. v. ingruit.
anslegaengrae (E, aslegenrae A, dat. sing. fem.) inpactae s. v. impactus.
anstigan (E, -ga A) termopilas s. v. Thermopylae. Cf. faestin vel anstigan.
ansuand (A, asuand E) hebesceret s. v. hebescit, asuand (E, assuant A) tabuisset s. v. tabeo. Cf. asundun; afulat ond asuunden.
ansuebidū (E, ensuebitum A) sopitis s. v. sopitus.
ansueop (E, asueus A incerta lectione) adflarat s. v. afflo.
aqueorna (E, aquorna A) scira (= sciurus). Cf. acuaerna.
araepsid (E, arepsit A) interceptum s. v. interceptus. Cf. refset.
arectio expedium (sed u in a mut. cod.) s. v. expedio: saxonicum subesse putat Schlutter coll. Corp. Chr. E 523 expediam arecio, ad Oros. VI, 22, 11 referens.
asclaecadun (i. e. aslaecadum) dimisis s. v. dimissus (demissis coni. Goetz). Cf. aslacudae.
ascrefan (= ascrepan) egerere s. v. egero 2.
aslacudae habitavit (i. e. hebetavit) s. v. hebetat. Cf. asclaecadun.
asuunden et asuundnan v. afulat ond asuunden.
atę vena 2. (= avena), atae (E, atte A) lolium.
auuaerdid (E, auuerdid A) vitiatum s. v. vitiatus.
auuel vel clauuo (E, clauo A) arpago s. v. harpago.
auunden torta s. v. tortus 2., auundre (E, auundenre A) suipan verbere torto. Cf. auundun.
ba v. an ba halbae s. v. an.
baanrift (E, baanryft A) tibialis s. v. tibiales.
baar berrus s. v. verris; caper.
baedendrae (E, bedaendrae A, part. fem. dat. gen. sing.) inpulsore s. v. impulsor.
baest (E, best A) tilia. Cf. lind vel baest s. v. lind.
barriggae (?) baruina (?), barice (?) braugina s. v. baruina.
bed (beod vel bred Michels) spathula. Cf. bedd?
będd culcites s. v. culcita. Cf. bed.
beel bustum, beel vel aad rogus.
begir bucina. Cf. beger et Wülcker-Wright p. 356, 24 (uaccinia verum esse vidit Schlutter).
beoso (A, baeso E) finicia s. v. phoeniceum.
beost colobostrum s. v. colostra; obestrum; lactantia s. v. lactantina.
beouaes (vel -uas) v. handful beouaes s. v. handful.
berc beta; bitulus (= betula). Cf. etiam birciae.
berecorn beręndae (E, berendae A) ptysones s. v. ptisana.
bidin tunna (at codex tinia i. e. tina). Cf. byden.
binoman ablata s. v. ablatum, binumini ablatā s. v. ablatum, binumni adempta s. v. ademptus.
biouuyrt marrubium (cf. hunae vel biouuyrt), biouuyrt (E, buuyrt A) apiastrum.
birednae (E, biraednae A) prodimur s. v. prodo.
bisceridae (A, bisceredae E) abdicavit s. v. abdĭco.
bisiuuidi uuerci (E, bisiuuisidi uerci A) opere plumario.
bismiridae (E, -da A) interlitam s. v. interlitus.
bisuicend (E, bisuiccend A) inpostorem s. v. impostor.
bituicn (E, bituichn A) aeldrum inter primores.
blidi (A, snel E) alacris s. v. alacer.
boc fau s. v. fagus. Cf. boeccae, beccae.
boecae (E, boeccae et boecce A) aesculus; fagus. Cf. beccae, boc.
boga fornix, bogan fornicem s v. fornix.
bol (i. e. bolstor) cervical s. v. cervicale.
bolla (E, bollae A) cutus s. v. cyathus; scyphus. Cf. bula.
boor salpeum (scalpeum cod. teste Gloggero, scalpellum coni. Goetz, scalprum Kluge).
bordremum rimis s. v. rima (alii coni. remis).
boretit (A, boręttit E) vibrat s. v. vibro.
braedlaestu aesc (A, brandlastęcus C, = bradlast aex) dolatura.
brandlastęcus v. braedlaestu aesc. brandrad (E, brondrad A) andena.
brectme (E, bretme A) vel cliderme (E, clidrinnae A) strepitu s. v. strepitus.
bred tabetum (= tapetum). Cf. Schlutter. Anglia XIV, 304.
bredisern (E, bredisaern A) scabellum (i. e. scalpellum, nam E scalbellum habet).
brigdils (A, bridils E, bridels C) bagula s. v. pagula.
briosa tabanus; asilo s. v. asilus.
brocc (E, broa A) taculus (= taxulus Goetz).
brocdaettendi (E, brogdaet hendi A, i. e. brogdaettendi) palpitans.
brodtbaca (A, borohaca E, = bordhaga Kluge) vel sceldhređa (A, sceldreda E) vel faenucae (A, iferucae E) testudo.
broec lumbare (cf. gyrdils vel broec s. v. gyrdels).
brog fideius s. v. fideiussor. Cf. borg?
brord (E, broord A) puntus s. v. punctum.
bruun burrum s. v. burrus; furvum s. v. furva. bruun (unus codex bruun locar) aquiluus s. v. aquilus.
brysti setes (= setas). Cf. brystae, byrst.
bucc (E, bua A) buccula. Cf. buuc.
buyrgenas v. dorh buyrgenas s. v. dorh.
byden bunia, bydin cupa. Cf. bidin.
byrgea sequester; praes et vas s. v. praes.
byrgeras v. dorh buyrgenas s. v. dorh.
byris scalpellum; byris vel thuearm (E, duaeram A) scalprum.
caebis (A, cebisae E) pelices s. v. pelex.
caest casma (= camsa) s. v. capsa; cest arca funebris; capsis; cista.
candelthuist (= candeltuist) emunctoria s. v. emunctorium.
cempa auctoratus, cempan (A, caempan E) gladiatores s. v. gladiator.
cetil caccabum s. v. caccabus; enunum s. v. aënulum (an = aënu[nu]m?).
ciisnis (E, ciinis A minus recte) fastidium.
cinaendi (E, cinendi A) hiulca s. v. hiulcus.
cisil (E, cisal A minus recte) glarea.
cistigian (= cyst.) munifica s. v. munificus.
clabre cf. clafre, rede clabre, huitti clabre.
claderstecca (A, cladersticca E) anate (= amite Buecheler).
clafre trifolia Gl. Werth. Gallée p. 344, quod addendum est Thesauro s. v. trifolium. Cf. clabre.
clata et clatacrop personacia, clatae blitum.
clauuo (E, clauo A) arpago s. v. harpago. V. auuel vel clauuo.
cleouuae (E, cleuuue A) glomer s. v. glomus.
clibecti (E, clibectis A) clivosum s. v. clivosus.
cliderme (E, clidrinnae A) strepitu s. v. strepitus. Cf. brectme vel cliderme.
clifae lappa; clifę id est clata, clatacrop personacia.
cneorissae (A, cneorissa E) sanguinis s. v. sanguis.
coerin defrutum; dulcis sapa. Cf. caerin. colþred (E, coldraed A) perpendiculum.
couel colus 2. (et colum); corbis. Cf. lorg.
erae et crę cornicula. Cf. sequ.
crauua cornix, crauuae cornacula s. v. cornicula.
cressa brittia; nasturcium; sinapio et sinapiones s. v. sinape, cressae sinapio s. v. sinape.
crince cuturno s. v. cothurnus. Cf. Anglia XIV, 308.
criopungae (E, criupungae A) obreptione s. v. obreptio.
crocha (E, chroca A, sing.) chytropodes. Cf. crog et crucae.
crog lagonam s. v. lagoena, croog lagoena.
crucae trulla; urciolum s. v. urceolus. Cf. crocha, crog.
cuscutan (E, cuscotae A) palumbes s. v. palumbis.
cynna cunabula s. v. cyciminium (saxonicum esse putant Gallée et Kluge).
daerm v. snaedil vel thearm. Cf. thearm.
deatlicostan: tha deatlicostan (E, da deudlicustan A) funestissima s. v. fu­nestus.
degn (A, thegn E) adseculam s. v. assecula.
deortuun v. edisc deortuun s. v. edisc. deudlicustan v. deatlicostan.
dinga v. aengi þinga, oeghuuelci đinga.
dixl arquamentum, dixlum (A, dislum E) temonibus s. v. temo.
dobend decrepitam s. v. decrepitus; dobeudi (A, dobgendi C = dobiendi) decrepita s. v. decrepitus.
dopaenid fulix s. v. fulica. V. ganot vel dopaenid.

dorh: dorh buyrgenas (A, þorch byrgeras E) per vispellones, dorh gifecilae (A, þrgifect E = þorch gifect) per duellium (explicatur per duellum), dorh (þorh E) ludgaet per pseuclothyrum, dorh obust (A, þorch obst E) per anticipationem.
drep fornice s. v. fornix. Cf. scelb vel clrep.
droccerum (oroccerum legit Glogger, v. p. 437) histrionibus s. v. histrio.
dropfaag (E, drofaxg A) stornus s. v. sturnus (sturninus conicit Kluge, Hesp. fam. 18 confert Schlutter).
duerg nanus vel pumilio s. v. nanus, duerh humiliamanus (= humilio, nanus).
durhere sualdam (= valvam), durheri (A, duerheri E) valva s. v. valvae.
earbetlicust (E, easbedlicust A) molestissimum s. v. molestus.
earendil (E, oerendil A) iubar. V. leoma vel oerendil.
earngeat (E, aerngeup A) arpa s. v. harpa.
earuuigga (E, aeruuica A) auriculum s. v. auricula.
edscaept palingeneseon (A, sed E palingenesean, unde alii palingenesian).
edualla (A, edwalla E) vertigo, eduella (E, eduelli A) toreuma.
efat reof (?) incusatio, efat reub epiphonema.
ellae (A, ellaen E) sambucus; elle sambuca s. v. sambucus.
endistaeb (C, staeb A) exito s. v. exitus.
eorisc scirpea; papyrum s. v. papyrus.
ęsdyni (efdyni coni. Steinmeyer) defexum s. v. devexus.
faam famfaluca. V. leasung vel faam.
faedum (A, faedun E) pangebant (i. e. pingebant) s. v. pango. Cf. faehit.
faehit (E, faethit A) pingit s. v. pingo. Cf. faedum.
faenucae (A, ifaerucae E, cf. p. 438 et Anglia XIV, 292) testudo. Cf. brodthaca.
faerbenu epifates s. v. epibatae. Cf. Schlutter, Anglia XIV, 291.
faerscribaen (E, faerscrifen A) addictus, faerslaeginum (A, fors leginũ E) profligatis s. v. profligatus.
faestiii (E, festin A) vel anstigan (E, anstiga A) Termopilas s. v. Thermopylae, faestinnum (dat. pl.) arcibus s. v. arx.
faetmaendi (E, faedmendi A) sinuosa s. v. sinuosus.
fala tabula (E, at A tabuIo, unde alii tubulo).
fealga occas s. v. occa cod. Ep. post V, 376, 20 (omissum in edit.).
fearn (E, feran A minus recte) filix.
felduuop (E, felduus A, felduop C) bradigabo (cf. add. p. 435 et Anglia XIV, 291).
felofearth (E, felufreth A) thorax (cf. add. p. 438 et Schlutter, Anglia XIV, 287).
feluspraeici (A, felospraeici E) trufulus (A, trifulus E, frivolus coni. Goetz. An trifarius ?).
feormad (E, caeormad A minus recte) fovit (= fovet) s. v. foveo.
ferred E post V, 378, 19 expl. proscribit, quod addendum est in Thes. s. v. proscribo.
ferth (E, fert A, i. e. ferht) probus.
fetod (E, fettad A minus recte) arcessitus.
fetor pedo vel paturum V, 381, 5 s. v. paedor (saxonicum fetor putant quidam, in his Schlutter, qui confert Corp. Chr. P. 253 pedo vel paturum feotur).
fex fucus 2. V, 360, 13 (saxonicum fex putant Zupitza et Schlutter contra Goetzium, qui confert σφήξ).
fifeldae spalagius s. v. sphalangius (= phal.).
fiit (i. e. fit vel fitt) amputatio. Cf. Schlutter. Anglia XIV, 292.
fina (E, pina A) marpicus et marsopicus (Martius picus coni. Goetz); lina vel higrae picus.
fingirdoccana (C, fingir docuna A) digitalium musculorum s. v. digitale.
fleah (E, floc A) pulix s. v. pulex.
fleti (E, fletu A minus recte) verberatrum. Cf. githuornae fleti.
flitad (A, flitat C) disceptant s. v. discepto.
flitere in ebhatis (ebhatum coni. Kluge) rabulus s. v. rabula.
floc (A, flooc E) platissa (et platesa sim.). Cf. fleah.
flugles bean v. fuglaes bean, fluglum v. stalu to fuglū.
foernissae: in foeruissae (E, infornissae A) in transmigrationem.
foot v. hraebnęs foot s. v. hraebn.
for (A, foor E) porcaster, for amisarius (= admissarius, v. add. p. 435).
foraeuuallū (E, foreuuallum A) vel tindū rostris s. v. rostrum.
fordh: a fordh (E, a forthe A minus recte) in dies crudesceret.
forslaegęn proflicta s. v. profligatus, ubi Orosii III, 17, 8 non I, 13, 1 confe­rendum in Thes. fuisse Schlutter monet.
forsoc (et forsooc) detractavit s. v. detracto.
fosturbearn (E, foetribarn A) alumnae s. v. alumnus.
fot v. hraebnęs foot s. v. hraebn.
fotmelum peculatus (saxonica interpre­tatio pertinet ad sequ. glossam pedetemptim).
fraam (E, from A) acris s. v. acer.
framadoenre (E, fram adoaendrae A, dat. sing.) remota s. v. remotum.
framlicae (E, fromlicae A) strenue, frecnis glus s. v. glutus.
fremu ( EA, freomo C, o prior supra scr.) beneficium.
frictrung (E, frictung A) ariolatus s. v. hariolatus.
fristmearc (E, fritmaerc A) intercapido s. v. intercapedo.
frost (E, frots A) gelum s. v. gelu.
frysca butio s. v. buteo. Cf. Anglia XIV, 293.
fuglaes bean (E, flugles bean A) vicium s. v. vicia. Cf. bean.
fultemendi (nom. sing. part. praes.) astipulatus, fultemendum (dat. sing. vel potius pl.) assessore s. v. assessor (sed A adsessores habet).
fyrpannae (E, fyrponnae A) vel herth (E, herd A) arula.
gaeadun (A, gihiodum E = giiodun, praeter.) adgrediuntur s. v. aggredior.
gaebuli aere alieno s. v. aes alienum, gebles monung exactio, gedębin gebil (A, gedaebeni geabuli C) debita pensio.
ganaendae (E, ganendae A) oscitantes s. v. oscitans.
ganot yel dopaenid fulix s. v. fulica, garlaec (E, garlec A) alium s. v. allium.
gataloc (E, gatanloc A) titulae s. v. tityrus (latetne subst. in -ile ut caprile, ovile?)
geacaes surae (E, gecaessarae A) accitulium s. v. accitula. Cf. iacessura.
geben uaes (A, gibaen uuaes E) inpendebatur s. v. impendo.
gebyrdid (A, gybyrdid E) clabatum s. v. clavata.
gecyndilican (i. e. gecyndilicum) genuino s. v. genuinus.
gefetodnae (E, gefetatnae A) acetum 3. = accitum (et habent codd. accetum, non acetum).
gegenta (i. e. gegenga) pedissequis s. v. pedisecus.
gegeruuednae (E, gegeruednae A) comparantem. Cf. gigeruuid.
gelu flavum s. v. flavus; gilbus, gelu (E, gelo A) crocus. Cf. aegergelu, geolu.
gemach (A, gimach E) improbus, gemengiungae v. gimaengiungae.
geolu (E, geholu A) venetum s. v. venetus. Cf. gelu?
geormantlab malva. V. cotuc vel geormantlab.
gerd: toch gerd (E, thoh gerd A) lentum vimen.

gerec liburnices, girec (crec coni. alii) dorcus s. v. cloricus. Kluge 'Angels. Leseb.' III. ed. p. 9 dorcas graece, item p. 4 liburnices graece conicit, vix recte; cf. Isid. orig. XIX, 1, 10, ubi dulcones navium genus est.
gerlicae (E, gernlicae A) annua s. v. annuus.
geruuae et gearuuae millefolium. gescanuuyrt v. giscaduuyrt.
gespan mauria, gespan (E, gespon A) murica.

gesuedradum exoleverunt s. v. exolesco, gesuidradrae (E, gisuderadae A. = gisuidradae)
constipuisse s. v. constipuit (vertitur defecit).
gesuirgion (E, gisuirgiam A = gisuirgian) consubrinus (= consobrinos? Goetz) s. v. consobrinus.
geuiif (= geuif) fortunam s. v. fortuna.
gibeataen (E, gebeatten A, gebeaten C) battuitum s. v. batutus.
gibrec (E, gebrec A) rheuma, gibrec (E, gibreec A) pituita.
gifecilae et gifect v. dorh gifecilae s. v. dorh.
gifraemith (E, gifremit A) provehit s. v. proveho. gifraemid (E, gifremid A) provecta s. v. provectus.
gifyrđro (A, gef. C) ditor s. v. ditare.
gigeruuid (E, gigarauuit A palaeotheod.) praetextatus. Cf. gegeruuednae.
gigiscdae (E, ḡ scdae A) oppillavit s. v. oppilo.
gigręmid et gigraemid (E, gigremid et gigremit A) lacessitus; irritatus in rixam.
giheldae (A, giheendae Gl. Corp. Chr.) exauctoravit s. v. exauctoro.
gihuuuelci uuaega (E gihuelci uuegi A) quocumque modo.
giindi (gimedi Kluge) conducti<ci>um s. v. conducticius.
gimaengdae (E, gimengdae A) infici s. v. inficio.
gimaengiungiae (E, gem̃giungae A recte) confusione s. v. confusio.
gimodae (E, gimode A) coniurati s. v. coniuratus.
giroedro (E, geroedra A) aplustra s. v. aplustria.
giroefa (E, geroefa A) commentariensis, giroefan (E, geroefan A) censores s. v. censor.
gisettae (E, girette A) condidit s. v. condo, a (A, đ E = đa) gisettan ordinatissimam s. v. ordinatus, þa gisettan (E, đagisettai A) inditas s. v. inditum.
gislog (A, tislog E) concidit s. v. concīdo.
githuornae (E, githuorne A) fleti lac tudiclatum.
gitiungi (E, getiung A) apparatione s. v. apparatio.
gitreeudae (E, getreudae A, sed e post r s. scr.) foederatus (A, foederatas E).
giuuaemmid (E, geuemmid A) infractus (infectus coni. Goetz).
gladinae (E, gledinae A) scilla s. v. squilla.
glida milba (= milva, fem. τοῦ milvus).
gliu facetiae s. v. facetia; in gliuuae (E, ingluviae A) in mimo, ubi saxonicum agnovit Schlutter coll. Corp. Chr. J. 228 in gliowe.
goduuebb (E, guoduueb A minus recte) fasces s. v. fascis.
grei glaucum s. v. glaucus. V. haeuui.
gremid (A, graemid E) lacessit s. v. lacesso.
grima scina; mascus s. v. masca. Cf. grina.
grimrodr (A, gimrodr C) dracontia s. v. draconitas.
grina scina (Glogger scena in L legit). Cf. grima.
groetu (sic, non groettu, E, gloeto A) convenio.
grona polopis (= polypus) et crinitus. Cf. granae.
grund suopa cartilago (Schlutter con­ferre iubet Anglia XIX, 104. XIV, 293. Journ. of Ph. XVII, 84).
grytt pollix (vel pullis) s. v. pollex = pollis vel puls.
gundaesuelgiae (E, gundae sueĭgae A) senecen (= senecion).
gyrdels brachiale, gyrdils vel broec lumbare, gyrdils hringe (A, gyrdisl rhingae E) legula s. v. lingula.
haam camissa s. v. camisia, ham (E, hom A) colobium.
haam (haā E, fam A, am coni. alii) cautere s. v. cauter.
haecid lucius, haecid (E, hecicl A) mugil.
haecilae (E, hecaeli A) paludamentum, haecilae (E, hecile A) vel lotha lacerna.
